Story 15: Error Handling and Loading States - COMPLETED

## Implementation Summary

### 1. Error Boundary Component
Created `/src/components/error-boundary.tsx`:
- Catches unexpected React component errors
- Prevents app crashes
- Shows user-friendly error message
- Provides "Try Again" and "Go Home" buttons
- Shows error details in development mode

### 2. Enhanced API Error Handling
Updated `/src/app/api/predict/route.ts`:
- Added specific error codes for all error types
- User-friendly error messages
- Differentiated error types:
  - AUTH_REQUIRED (401)
  - MISSING_TEXT / EMPTY_TEXT (400)
  - TEXT_TOO_LONG (400)
  - RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED (429) with upgrade prompt
  - NETWORK_ERROR (503)
  - TIMEOUT_ERROR (504)
  - AI_ERROR (500)
  - PARSE_ERROR (500)
  - VALIDATION_ERROR (500)
  - INTERNAL_ERROR (500)
- Added retryable flags for transient errors

### 3. Toast Notifications
Updated `/src/app/predict/predict-page-client.tsx`:
- Integrated sonner toast notifications
- Success toast on prediction completion
- Error toasts with specific messages
- Action buttons for:
  - Retry (for network errors)
  - Log In (for auth errors)
- Wrapped in ErrorBoundary

### 4. Enhanced Error States
Updated `/src/components/predict/prediction-result.tsx`:
- Different error UIs for different error types:
  - Rate limit errors show "Upgrade" prompt
  - Network errors show "Retry" button
  - General errors show "Try Again"
- Added informational message for rate limits
- Toast notification on successful copy
- Error toast on failed copy

### 5. Form Validation
Updated `/src/components/predict/tweet-input.tsx`:
- Added inline error display
- Visual error state (red border)
- Error icon and message below input
- Real-time validation as user types
- Character limit enforcement

Updated `/src/app/predict/predict-page-client.tsx`:
- Validation before API call
- Inline error messages
- Clear error on user input
- Toast notifications for validation errors

### 6. Loading States
Already implemented with skeleton loaders in prediction-result.tsx:
- Skeleton for viral score gauge
- Skeleton for factor breakdown
- Skeleton for suggestions
- Loading button state with spinner
- Proper feedback during analysis

## All Acceptance Criteria Met

✅ API errors show user-friendly messages
✅ Rate limit errors (429) show clear "limit reached" message with upgrade prompt
✅ Network errors show retry option
✅ Loading states show appropriate feedback (spinner, skeleton)
✅ Form validation errors are displayed inline
✅ Toast notifications for success/error feedback

